# .cursorrules

rules:
  - description: "Always write clear, maintainable, and reusable code."
  - description: "Use consistent naming conventions: camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for classes/types."
  - description: "Follow language-specific style guides: PEP8 for Python, ESLint for JavaScript/TypeScript, Prettier for formatting."
  - description: "Comment complex or non-trivial code blocks, explaining purpose and logic."
  - description: "Avoid magic numbers; use named constants or configuration files."
  - description: "Do not commit sensitive information (e.g., API keys, passwords) to the repository."
  - description: "Write functions and components with a single responsibility."
  - description: "Limit function and method sizes to improve readability and testability."
  - description: "Use modern, secure, and actively maintained libraries."
  - description: "Validate user inputs and handle errors gracefully."
  - description: "Document public APIs, endpoints, and reusable modules clearly."
  - description: "Write unit and integration tests for critical logic."
  - description: "Ensure code is compatible with the project's target runtime versions (e.g., Node.js, Python, etc.)."
  - description: "Optimize for readability over premature performance tweaks."
  - description: "Follow Git best practices: small, descriptive commits; meaningful commit messages; avoid large monolithic changes."

